## Output Preview

Example session of the mini shell running in the terminal:

```
tsh> pwd
/home/user/projects/mini-shell

tsh> ls
mini_shell.c
README.md

tsh> ls -la
total 16
drwxr-xr-x  2 user user 4096 Jun 19 12:28 .
drwxr-xr-x 10 user user 4096 Jun 19 12:20 ..
-rw-r--r--  1 user user 2200 Jun 19 12:28 mini_shell.c
-rw-r--r--  1 user user  900 Jun 19 12:28 README.md

tsh> echo Hello World
Hello World

tsh> exit
Exiting shell...
```

This demonstrates how the shell reads user commands, creates a child process, and executes system programs using `execvp()`.
